If $t \typeof T$ and $t \stepsto t'$, then $t' \typeof T$
\end{theorem}

The induction hypothesis is: if $t_0 \typeof T_0$, $t_0 \stepsto
t_0'$, and $t_0 \typeof T_0 \subderv t \typeof T$, then $t'_0 \typeof
